# GPP input file
#
# Hash tag at start of line is comment.  Empty lines are ok, but there
# should only be a single line with content; bash-style variables are
# not supported as the non-comment content of this file is fed in as
# the arguments to GPP.
#
# GPP is strange in that there cannot be any space between option
# flags and their arguments; e.g. -a2.5 is ok, while -a 2.5 is not.
#
# Initial settings:
#
# -ogpp_out.bos -a2.35 -b2.35 -c2.35 -f0.97 -P0x1b -R36557 gpp_in.bos
#
# OPTIONS:

# Output:
-ogpp_out.bos

# Smear scale factors:
# -a: DOCA1
# -b: DOCA2
# -c: DOCA3
# -f: SC
-a2.35
-b2.35
-c2.35
-f0.97

# Master processing flags:
#
# -P: binary number with the following bit-flags
#
# Bitwise process flags
# Individual flags are
# 0x1     DC - Remove dead wires
# 0x2     Smear DC values
# 0x4     SC - Remove dead paddles
# 0x8     Smear SC values
# 0x10    Create CALL Bank
# 0x20    Smear Tagger timeing
# 0x40    Remove bad tagger conters
# 0x80    IC - Remove dead IC channels
# 0x100   Smear IC values
-P0x1b
# -R: Run number
-R36557

# Input file (MUST BE THE FINAL ARGUMENT)
gpp_in.bos
